                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4152.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Chihuahua</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Chihuahua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-07T10:00:00-07:04">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1912—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conference with Orozco June 4. He totally denied responsibility for threats
                    against Americans made in the recent manifesto reported in my May 29, noon; he
                    made apologies therefor, promised to rectify all pending complaints. Little to
                    be expected therefrom, however.</p>
                <p>Rebels announce intention to negotiate a loan $10,000,000 (Mexican) New York.
                    Unlikely story, intended to cheer up partisans.</p>
                <p>All Americans prepared to leave if danger appears imminent.</p>
                <p>Small arms, 50,000 rounds, received from Paso del Norte by rebels yesterday</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Letcher.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
